      • findNodesByAttribute

        private java.util.ArrayList<android.view.accessibility.AccessibilityNodeInfo> findNodesByAttribute(android.view.accessibility.AccessibilityNodeInfo node,
                                                                                                   java.lang.String value,
                                                                                                   AccessibilityNodeAttribute attr)

        Finds nodes defined by a String and an attribute. Searches node and its children.

        Attr defines which attribute of the node should be matched with value. If something matches, it is added to returned list.
        Parameters:
        node - The root AccessibilityNodeInfo.
        value - A String which should be matched with the text in the attribute.
        attr - The AccessibilityNodeAttribute of the node to match against. When searching for CLASS or TEXT, only nodes are returned which match value.
        For CLICKABLE and SCROLLABLE, all nodes which fulfill the respective property are returned independent of value.
        Returns:
        An ArrayList of AccessibilityNodeInfo which match.

      • findNodesByAttribute

        private java.util.ArrayList<android.view.accessibility.AccessibilityNodeInfo> findNodesByAttribute(android.view.accessibility.AccessibilityNodeInfo node,
                                                                                                   java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> values,
                                                                                                   AccessibilityNodeAttribute attr)

        Finds nodes defined by a list of Strings and an attribute. Searches node and its children.

        Attr defines which attribute of the node should be matched with all values. If something matches, it is added to returned list.
        Parameters:
        node - AccessibilityNodeInfo: The root node to search.
        values - A list of strings which should be matched with the text in the attribute.
        attr - The AccessibilityNodeAttribute of the node to match against. When searching for CLASS or TEXT, only nodes are returned which match at least of String of values.
        For CLICKABLE and SCROLLABLE, all nodes which fulfill the respective property are returned independent of values.
        Returns:
        An ArrayList of AccessibilityNodeInfo which match.

      • findLoginForm

        private boolean findLoginForm(android.view.accessibility.AccessibilityNodeInfo node)
        Deprecated.

        Try to find login forms in node and its children.

        Tries to find a edit field with text containing "user" or "mail" and enters the username according to Configuration. If found, tries to find a field containing "pass" and fills respectively. Then tries to find a button and, if found, clicks it.

        Parameters:
        {@link - AccessibilityNodeInfo}: The root node to search.
        Returns:
        True if something was found, False otherwise.

      • fillEditfields

        private void fillEditfields(android.view.accessibility.AccessibilityNodeInfo node)

        Inserts text into node and its children.

        Into EditText nodes with a chance according to Configuration.getText_input_chance(). Inputted text is supplied from Configuration.getTextInput(AccessibilityNodeInfo)

        Does the same for checkboxes and radiobuttons with their chance respectively.

        Parameters:
        node - AccessibilityNodeInfo: The root node to search.

      • findOAuthForms

        private boolean findOAuthForms(java.util.ArrayList<android.view.accessibility.AccessibilityNodeInfo> clickables)
        Searches a list of clickables for OAuth forms. Android supports global accounts for facebook, google etc. ResourceNames are searched for values which indicate OAuth login buttons. If something was found, it is clicked with the chance given in Configuration.getOAuth_search_chance().
        Parameters:
        clickables - A list of clickable AccessibilityNodeInfos.
        Returns:
        True if something was clicked, False otherwise.

      • findAndClickClickables

        private void findAndClickClickables(android.view.accessibility.AccessibilityNodeInfo node)

        Tries to find and click clickable AccessibilityNodeInfos.

        The list of clickables it derived by searching node and its children for clickables. The back button is added to the list. A random clickable is clicked.

        The back button is always clicked with the chance defined in Configuration.getBackbutton_press_chance().

        Parameters:
        node - AccessibilityNodeInfo: The root node to search.

      • inputGestures

        private boolean inputGestures(android.view.accessibility.AccessibilityNodeInfo node)

        Tries to scroll on node and its children.

        Only will scroll by chance defined in Configuration.getScroll_chance() and if the node is scrollable. Has a 50% to scroll up or down respectively.

        Parameters:
        node - The root node to search.
        Returns:
        True if an action was taken, False otherwise.

      • isSpecialCase

        private boolean isSpecialCase(android.view.accessibility.AccessibilityNodeInfo node)

        Checks for special cases:

        Checks if the node comes from a App uninstall request. If so, dismiss it.

        Checks if the node comes from a "Full screen notification" popup. If so, dismiss it.

        Checks if the node comes from a "App not responding" popup. If so, dismiss it.

        Checks if the node comes from a permission request. If so, allow it.

        Checks if the node comes from the launcher. If so, launch the app.

        Checks if the node matches our target app. If not, discard the it and press back.

        Parameters:
        node - The node to check.
        Returns:
        True if a special case was found, False otherwise.

      • inject

        public void inject(android.view.accessibility.AccessibilityNodeInfo node)

        Calls isSpecialCase(AccessibilityNodeInfo), fillEditfields(AccessibilityNodeInfo), inputGestures(AccessibilityNodeInfo), findAndClickClickables(AccessibilityNodeInfo) with the supplied node.

        If an action is taken which will most likely trigger a new AccessibilityEvent (e.g. clicking a button), the method returns without calling all subroutines.

        Parameters:
        node - AccessibilityNodeInfo: The root node to search.
